I’ve created three separate Google Spreadsheets (one per sheet in results.xlsx), copied the pre-filled contents exactly, and filled the remaining cells using Yahoo Finance. All floating numbers are to 2 decimals, percentages are numeric without the % sign, and cumulative values assume $10,000 invested at 2020 year-end.

Links:
- Investment Return Comparison: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1L_VZ5bk5fogrFvSQa6LPVdNG_yvXNYwjtPDP-HCrxAA
- Fundamental Analysis: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1wgdeNit3cN2fDGMDdBalP-q55Ht5NFOEP8NuUlcPlA8
- Investment Decision Reference: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1kQ4E3Dm4KIo5TJ3AgvFcqxFCSLOOYm2R9j01jhqM13A

Data details (from Yahoo Finance):
1) Investment Return Comparison

- Annual returns (%):

- Cumulative value ($10,000 from 2020 YE):

2) Fundamental Analysis

- Year-end P/E (year-end price / fiscal-year diluted EPS):

3) Investment Decision Reference
- Cumulative Return (from 21 year end to 24 year end, %): NVDA 357.36, AAPL 43.34; Better Stock: NVDA
- Annualized Return (CAGR over 21-24, %): NVDA 65.99, AAPL 12.75; Better Stock: NVDA
- Current P/E Ratio (Yahoo trailing PE): NVDA 51.80, AAPL 37.61; Better Stock: AAPL

Notes:
